## üíª CODING STANDARDS

### Swift Best Practices
- ALWAYS use async/await for async operations
- Use @MainActor for ALL UI updates
- Use @Observable for ViewModels (iOS 17+)
- Use SwiftData for persistence
- Implement proper error handling with Result type
- Use SwiftUI over UIKit (UIKit only when critical)

### Code Organization
- Max 300 lines per file
- Group with // MARK: - comments
- Use extensions for protocol conformance
- Separate: Views, ViewModels, Models, Services
- Place reusable components in Core/Components

### Naming Conventions
- Views: *View.swift (e.g., OrbitalView.swift)
- ViewModels: *ViewModel.swift
- Models: *Model.swift or entity name
- Services: *Service.swift
- Extensions: *+Extension.swift

